id: pm-jcyn
title: "Unified extension test harness (createExtensionTestHarness): one fluent fixture binding all activate/assert/invoke/deactivate SDK helpers"
description: "Capstone for the now-complete SDK package-author testing surface. Individual helpers (activateExtensionForTest, assertRegistered*, runRegistered*, deactivateExtensionForTest) each force authors to thread the correct sub-registry (activation.registrations vs .commands vs .hooks vs .parsers vs the whole activation), which is a footgun (wrong sub-registry yields a confusing 'available: (none)' error). createExtensionTestHarness activates a module once and returns a fluent, destructurable fixture that binds every assert/run helper to the right sub-registry and exposes deactivate(), so writing a package test no longer requires knowing pm's internal registry layout. Aligns with project-management=context-management: minimizes boilerplate/token cost for agents authoring packages and makes package creation as easy and customizable as possible."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk",dx
created_at: "2026-06-22T09:25:53.160Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-22T10:45:45.679Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Added createExtensionTestHarness + ExtensionTestHarness to src/sdk/testing.ts (re-exported via the sdk barrel and @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing). 100% coverage (4838 tests), docstring/static/docs gates green, manual end-to-end smoke against built dist passed. Docs updated in docs/SDK.md and docs/EXTENSIONS.md."
