comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T09:47:49.750Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #339 opened (branch feat/sdk-extension-test-harness, commit 76ce93d6): createExtensionTestHarness capstone. Full coverage 100/100/100/100 (4838 tests), all gates green, manual dist smoke passed. Triggered @codex / @gemini-code-assist / CodeRabbit review; awaiting CI + AI-bot rounds."
  "2026-06-22T10:03:36.607Z",claude-code-agent,"Review round 1 (PR #339): Gemini fail-fast finding (medium) FIXED in commit 9f19c9b4 — harness now throws a descriptive error on activation.failed instead of returning empty registries (the 'available: (none)' footgun); +2 branch tests, testing.ts stays 100/100/100/100. Declined 2 CodeRabbit false-positives with reasons: (1) per-change tracker-ref in docs — CONTRIBUTING.md:152 is PR-description-scoped (satisfied) and no doc carries such a ref; (2) add 'exporters' capability — importers/exporters intentionally share the 'importers' capability (docs/SDK.md table + existing tests), 'exporters' is not in KNOWN_EXTENSION_CAPABILITIES by design. Re-triggered Codex/Gemini/CodeRabbit."
  "2026-06-22T10:25:16.405Z",claude-code-agent,"Review round 2 (PR #339): Gemini suggested simplifying harness.deactivate (destructure deactivateTimeoutMs with =\\{\\} default vs optional chaining) — APPLIED in commit 244ac53a, behavior identical, testing.ts stays 100/100/100/100. CodeRabbit no new findings; prior 2 declines stand. Re-triggered bots."
  "2026-06-22T10:45:45.679Z",claude-code-agent,"Review rounds 3-4 + MERGED (PR #339, merge commit 8861c307): R3 — adopted file's options-object convention for deactivate (deactivateOptions = {} + .deactivateTimeoutMs), CodeRabbit endorsed it. R4 — Gemini oscillated back to the round-2 inline-destructure form it had asked me to remove; declined (functionally equivalent, current form is file-consistent + null-safe for typed callers + 100% branch-covered, flip-flop would never converge). Final state: CI 15/15 green (Sourcery rate-limited/skipped, Codex not connected), CodeRabbit full review finished with no new findings + 2 earlier items declined-with-reason. Squash-free merge commit to main; auto-release will pick up this closed Feature in the next [Unreleased] cut."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T09:43:46.651Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented createExtensionTestHarness + ExtensionTestHarness interface in src/sdk/testing.ts (re-exported via src/sdk/index.ts and the @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing subpath). The factory activates a module once and returns a fluent fixture whose 16 assert*/12 run* methods + deactivate() are pre-bound to the correct activation sub-registry; methods use closures (no `this`) so they are safe to destructure. Added 4 focused tests (sdk-index.spec.ts) covering every method via one rich fixture extension + a barrel-equivalence lock. testing.ts at 100/100/100/100 coverage (415 stmts, 287 branches, 158 fns). Docs updated: docs/SDK.md (recommended-entry paragraph + exports list + example) and docs/EXTENSIONS.md (in-place, under 450-line cap). typecheck + quality:static + quality:docs-skills green. Manual end-to-end smoke (temp dir, symlinked package, real @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing import) PASSED: assert/run/hook/importer/destructure/deactivate all work against the built dist."
close_reason: "Shipped createExtensionTestHarness: a fluent ExtensionTestHarness fixture that activates a module once and binds all 16 assert*/12 run* helpers + deactivate() to the correct activation sub-registry, so package authors never thread activation.registrations/.commands/.hooks by hand."
